WEBVTT

00:34.469 --> 00:35.687
Where...

00:35.731 --> 00:38.299
the hell am I?

00:40.344 --> 00:42.520
Hello?!

00:45.741 --> 00:48.483
I was just like you.

00:49.484 --> 00:51.268
20 minutes ago.

00:51.312 --> 00:54.663
Woke up here in shock,
no idea where I was.

00:55.707 --> 00:57.709
I came over, gave you a nudge.

00:59.363 --> 01:02.105
But you were busy producing
a puddle of drool.

01:02.149 --> 01:04.977
Honestly, who am I to interrupt?

01:08.720 --> 01:11.114
Gray.

01:11.158 --> 01:12.855
It's an interesting choice.

01:12.898 --> 01:15.814
It's supposed to be
psychologically oppressive.

01:16.859 --> 01:18.382
But I like gray.

01:18.426 --> 01:19.514
So there.

01:25.607 --> 01:27.652
I know you.

01:28.697 --> 01:30.090
You're The Merchant.

01:30.133 --> 01:32.657
You tried to kill Desi.

01:32.701 --> 01:35.095
Who?

01:35.138 --> 01:36.444
Listen, I'm...

01:36.487 --> 01:38.620
I'm genuinely sorry.

01:38.663 --> 01:40.448
I...

01:40.491 --> 01:43.799
I-I meet a lot of people
in my line of work.

01:43.842 --> 01:45.453
So...

01:45.496 --> 01:47.498
if you wouldn't mind
being a bit more specific.

01:49.413 --> 01:52.721
Where the hellare we?!

01:52.764 --> 01:54.375
I have no idea.

01:54.418 --> 01:55.376
You're a liar!

01:55.419 --> 01:56.725
What do you wantfrom me?

01:58.422 --> 02:00.381
Uh...

02:00.424 --> 02:02.296
I want you to let go.

02:02.339 --> 02:04.298
Please.

02:05.560 --> 02:08.563
Clearly, you and I are
in the same predicament.

02:08.606 --> 02:11.392
It's just I'd say I'm
handling it a bit better.

02:11.435 --> 02:13.568
Eh? Without all the
grabbing and shouting

02:13.611 --> 02:16.658
and toxic masculinity.

02:21.880 --> 02:23.273
This coming from the man

02:23.317 --> 02:25.188
who murdered a woman
in a soccer stadium.

02:26.233 --> 02:27.886
Was that you?

02:27.930 --> 02:30.541
On the soccer pitch.

02:30.585 --> 02:32.978
Oh, right.

02:33.022 --> 02:35.720
You're that teenager
from the, um...

02:35.764 --> 02:38.506
from the Falcon organization.

02:39.550 --> 02:40.551
Fal...

02:40.595 --> 02:42.988
Phoenix... Foundation.

02:43.032 --> 02:46.035
You're the criminally insaneweasel
on the run from Codex.

02:46.078 --> 02:47.384
I don't like that word.

02:47.428 --> 02:49.560
What, "weasel"?"Insane."

02:49.604 --> 02:52.302
It's a simple word
stupid people use

02:52.346 --> 02:53.714
when they can't face
the complexities

02:53.738 --> 02:54.783
of the human psyche.

02:54.826 --> 02:57.873
"Sociopath"...
There's another one.

02:57.916 --> 02:59.396
It's like, "Everyone, calm down.

02:59.440 --> 03:01.746
Stop trying to label me."

03:01.790 --> 03:05.010
What was the last thing
that you remember?

03:05.054 --> 03:07.622
I was drinking a cup of tea,

03:07.665 --> 03:08.753
oolong,

03:08.797 --> 03:11.626
in a Shanghai cafe.

03:11.669 --> 03:13.889
Everything went dark.

03:13.932 --> 03:16.457
I woke up, I was being
transported somewhere,

03:16.500 --> 03:18.023
then held.

03:20.025 --> 03:21.375
I really don't know.

03:21.418 --> 03:23.072
I just...

03:23.115 --> 03:26.031
found myself coming to here.

03:27.555 --> 03:28.860
You?

03:28.904 --> 03:31.341
I was in China, tracking you.

03:31.385 --> 03:33.038
Oh, were you?

03:33.082 --> 03:36.433
Well, serves you right, then,
doesn't it?

03:36.477 --> 03:38.914
You're bleeding, by the way.

03:45.312 --> 03:46.878
Oh, look.

03:46.922 --> 03:49.185
I've got one, too.
Twinsies.

03:50.969 --> 03:52.710
There's something sewn in

03:52.754 --> 03:54.495
under the skin.Please.

03:54.538 --> 03:56.584
Please stop poking it.

03:56.627 --> 03:59.064
It's a planted port.

03:59.108 --> 04:01.589
Oh, you mean
there's an IV in here?

04:01.632 --> 04:03.591
Yeah.

04:03.634 --> 04:06.811
Yeah, that explains
why we're so disoriented.

04:07.943 --> 04:10.337
We've been drugged.

04:11.381 --> 04:12.730
Judging by the stitches,

04:12.774 --> 04:14.906
I'd say we've been here a week.

04:14.950 --> 04:17.518
I don't...

04:17.561 --> 04:19.433
I don't want to be in this cell.

04:19.476 --> 04:21.957
I really...

04:22.000 --> 04:25.352
I really don't want
to be in this cell.

04:27.354 --> 04:30.661
Yeah, well, neither do I.

04:30.705 --> 04:34.622
And I got a bad
feelingnobody's coming for us.

04:34.665 --> 04:38.539
Which means our only hope
of getting out of here...

04:38.582 --> 04:40.584
is each other.

04:43.326 --> 04:45.285
♪

05:12.616 --> 05:14.575
Got it.

05:14.618 --> 05:16.054
Got what?

05:16.098 --> 05:18.622
Oh, t... I told you
to stop poking that.

05:18.666 --> 05:19.841
That's just...

05:19.884 --> 05:21.364
Try...

05:21.408 --> 05:23.279
Trying to...

05:23.323 --> 05:25.629
make it more difficult

05:25.673 --> 05:27.196
for our captorsto drug me.

05:29.111 --> 05:30.721
Keeping hold of that, are we?

05:30.765 --> 05:32.723
Never know.
Might come in handy.

05:36.031 --> 05:37.337
No, I kn...

05:37.380 --> 05:38.425
I know who you are.

05:38.468 --> 05:39.730
You're that bloke

05:39.774 --> 05:41.602
that makes things
out of things, right?

05:41.645 --> 05:43.299
You're like,

05:43.343 --> 05:45.214
"I-I got a toothbrush,

05:45.257 --> 05:47.782
"I got some bubblegum, some
duct tape and some earwax,

05:47.825 --> 05:49.218
"and, hey, hey, presto,
I just made

05:49.261 --> 05:50.524
an aeroplane."

05:52.874 --> 05:54.658
Let go of me!
I don't speak crazy!

05:54.702 --> 05:56.399
Get him off me!
Get him off me!

05:56.443 --> 05:58.183
Get him off me! Calm down! Calm down!

05:58.227 --> 05:59.247
I can't calm down! Just...

05:59.271 --> 06:01.143
listento my voice, okay?

06:01.186 --> 06:03.624
- I find it irritating.
- Please be quiet.

06:05.669 --> 06:07.236
My name is Angus.

06:07.279 --> 06:08.629
What's your name?

06:14.330 --> 06:17.289
What are you trying to do, get
me to laugh myself to death?

06:17.333 --> 06:20.031
That's terrible, that is.

06:20.075 --> 06:23.600
What, they named you after beef?

06:23.644 --> 06:26.647
Pretty sureit's Scottish.

06:30.738 --> 06:33.610
My name's Clive.

06:33.654 --> 06:35.525
It's not an alias.

06:35.569 --> 06:38.702
Well, Clive, just...

06:38.746 --> 06:40.225
make sureto breathe deep...

06:40.269 --> 06:42.750
Why don't you shut up and
let me listen to the birds?

06:44.404 --> 06:46.754
I like listening to the birds.

06:49.365 --> 06:50.671
What birds?

06:50.714 --> 06:52.673
Shh.

06:52.716 --> 06:55.110
Listen to that.
You hear that?

06:57.199 --> 06:59.984
That's a reed parrotbill.

07:03.205 --> 07:04.728
And the other one, the...

07:04.772 --> 07:06.164
That's a bunting.

07:07.209 --> 07:08.384
That'sa Tibetan bunting.

07:12.432 --> 07:14.477
I think we're still in China.

07:22.093 --> 07:23.704
Birds migrate,

07:23.747 --> 07:26.271
but there is a way to confirm
if what you're saying is true.

07:32.887 --> 07:34.062
What are you doing?

07:36.673 --> 07:37.848
Shh!

07:47.118 --> 07:48.337
Oi. N-No, no, no.

07:50.557 --> 07:52.080
Oh, that's incredible.

07:52.123 --> 07:55.170
This pipe most likely runs
throughout the entire prison.

07:55.213 --> 07:56.301
So...

07:56.345 --> 07:58.173
if I create a seal between

07:58.216 --> 07:59.609
my ear and this hole...

07:59.653 --> 08:02.612
No. No,
it's incredibly unhygienic.

08:02.656 --> 08:05.223
Your face is right next
to that bucket of wee.

08:09.140 --> 08:10.707
Speaking Mandarin.

08:10.751 --> 08:12.100
I told you.

08:12.143 --> 08:13.188
I told you, didn't I?

08:13.231 --> 08:15.320
So we arein China.

08:15.364 --> 08:17.148
When are they coming for you?

08:17.192 --> 08:18.846
Who?

08:18.889 --> 08:20.108
The Phoenix people.

08:20.151 --> 08:21.588
Yeah, they're not coming.

08:23.241 --> 08:24.416
Great.

08:26.462 --> 08:28.203
So what now?

08:28.246 --> 08:30.161
Why don't we talk
about the people

08:30.205 --> 08:32.337
who did this to us?

08:32.381 --> 08:34.078
Let's talk about Codex.

08:34.122 --> 08:36.167
What, you think this is Codex?

08:36.211 --> 08:38.953
How else do you explain the
twoof us in a cell together?

08:38.996 --> 08:41.346
I shut down their
match fixing operation.

08:41.390 --> 08:43.174
You lost a lot of money
for them.

08:43.218 --> 08:45.350
Our common enemy is Codex.

08:45.394 --> 08:47.439
Yeah, but I paid them back
since then, didn't I?

08:47.483 --> 08:48.615
And I've kept

08:48.658 --> 08:50.617
in their good graces.

08:50.660 --> 08:53.358
This is not Codex.

08:54.621 --> 08:56.448
Someone's coming.

09:23.388 --> 09:25.303
♪

09:34.399 --> 09:36.227
Well?

09:37.272 --> 09:38.316
I think he bought it.

09:38.360 --> 09:39.753
Hook, line and sinker.

09:39.796 --> 09:40.754
He's got a thingabout birds.

09:40.797 --> 09:41.885
Is that gonna bea problem?

09:41.929 --> 09:43.931
The techs have done
their research.

09:43.974 --> 09:45.628
Hey. You okay?

09:45.672 --> 09:47.761
Yeah. Yeah.

09:47.804 --> 09:48.979
I need a reset on the rat.

09:49.023 --> 09:50.415
Who's got the rat food?

09:50.459 --> 09:53.636
And, Riley, I needthose
weather effects yesterday.

09:53.680 --> 09:55.246
Almost there.

09:55.290 --> 09:58.380
I see you're finally connecting
with someone emotionally.

09:58.423 --> 09:59.511
Good for you.

10:04.212 --> 10:07.911
Exactly how much moneydid
you spend on this circus?

10:07.955 --> 10:09.826
Well,

10:09.870 --> 10:11.611
if Codex find a way to wipe out

10:11.654 --> 10:13.395
a quarter of the
Earth's population,

10:13.438 --> 10:16.398
I don't think I'm gonna care
too much about my bank balance.

10:16.441 --> 10:17.617
Is this gonna work?

10:17.660 --> 10:20.489
I don't know.

10:20.532 --> 10:21.988
Every time I think
we've knocked them back,

10:22.012 --> 10:24.449
they seem to come
back at us stronger.

10:24.493 --> 10:26.408
We need intel. We need...

10:26.451 --> 10:27.931
we need to get ahead of them.

10:27.975 --> 10:30.368
Because, without that,

10:30.412 --> 10:33.154
I'm running out of hope.

10:33.197 --> 10:35.547
♪

10:48.169 --> 10:50.519
Does that hurt? No.

10:51.955 --> 10:54.218
You know you don't have
to try to impress me.

10:54.262 --> 10:55.829
You already got me
naked in a shower.

10:55.872 --> 10:57.569
That's a good point.

10:57.613 --> 10:59.876
I'm sorry The Merchant's
bodyguard stabbed you

10:59.920 --> 11:02.400
in the neck before I could
take her out with a tranq dart.

11:02.444 --> 11:03.943
There's somethingyou don't hear every day.

11:03.967 --> 11:05.360
No.

11:06.927 --> 11:08.798
You know,

11:08.842 --> 11:11.932
we have a few more
hours of freedom

11:11.975 --> 11:14.108
before Matty begins
her interrogation.

11:15.457 --> 11:17.720
Hey, guys, sorry to interrupt.

11:17.764 --> 11:19.940
Um, Matty wants us back
at the Phoenix.

11:19.983 --> 11:21.593
Something to do
with The Merchant?

11:21.637 --> 11:24.161
Yeah, we will, uh... we'll get dressed.

11:24.205 --> 11:25.641
All righty.

11:29.210 --> 11:30.690
No.

11:33.780 --> 11:35.825
Taylor, what's going on?
You know the burner phone

11:35.869 --> 11:38.088
we pulled from The
Merchant in China? Yeah.

11:38.132 --> 11:39.263
Techs found

11:39.307 --> 11:41.526
something unexpected.

11:41.570 --> 11:45.617
Encrypted messages sent
from The Merchant to Codex.

11:45.661 --> 11:47.421
MacGYVER: That doesn't make any sense.
After he lost

11:47.445 --> 11:49.621
Codex all that money in Milan,
they wanted him dead.

11:49.665 --> 11:51.643
Yeah, swapping messages
indicates that they've kissed

11:51.667 --> 11:53.625
and made up. That means...

11:53.669 --> 11:54.907
The Merchant possibly knows more

11:54.931 --> 11:56.454
about Codex
than we first thought.

11:56.498 --> 11:58.674
Like the location
of their new headquarters.

11:58.718 --> 12:00.807
We're not gonna be able
to decrypt those messages.

12:00.850 --> 12:02.417
I've been working
on Major Frost's phone

12:02.460 --> 12:04.811
since the NORAD attack.
I've got nothing.

12:04.854 --> 12:06.073
Well, then, we better

12:06.116 --> 12:07.509
start working on him.

12:07.552 --> 12:10.294
He's out cold
in the interrogation room.

12:10.338 --> 12:11.774
Total sensory deprivation.

12:11.818 --> 12:13.036
Taylor,

12:13.080 --> 12:14.385
you're with me.
The rest of you,

12:14.429 --> 12:15.691
I want you listening in.

12:15.735 --> 12:16.648
Wait.

12:16.692 --> 12:17.911
That man

12:17.954 --> 12:19.608
was tranquilized. He has no idea

12:19.651 --> 12:21.610
who took himor where he is.

12:21.653 --> 12:22.785
Right?

12:22.829 --> 12:24.023
So we can use that
to our advantage.

12:24.047 --> 12:25.440
Of course.

12:25.483 --> 12:27.485
Messing with him is part
of the interrogation.No.

12:27.529 --> 12:28.965
We don't interrogate him.

12:29.009 --> 12:30.488
We help him.

12:30.532 --> 12:31.751
Look, The Merchant may sound

12:31.794 --> 12:33.154
like a derangedchat show host, but

12:33.187 --> 12:34.797
he's highly intelligent,

12:34.841 --> 12:37.060
manipulative...
and trained by Codex.

12:37.104 --> 12:39.541
Traditional interrogationwon't work on him.

12:39.584 --> 12:41.848
Exactly what do you have
in mind?

12:43.893 --> 12:46.591
Uh, why are wein the storage bay?

12:46.635 --> 12:48.942
This is where we play
laser tag and defuse bombs.

12:48.985 --> 12:51.727
Right. We canput the, uh...

12:51.771 --> 12:53.773
cell block here,

12:53.816 --> 12:57.994
hallway here, a little bit
of, uh, fake sunlight.

12:58.038 --> 12:59.430
This'll be perfect.

12:59.474 --> 13:01.432
You want to build a prison?

13:01.476 --> 13:04.958
A prison set...
for our beautiful con.

13:05.001 --> 13:06.524
The Merchant isn'tgoing to wake up

13:06.568 --> 13:07.850
in the Phoenixinterrogation room.

13:07.874 --> 13:10.093
He's going to wake upin
a cell somewhere else.

13:10.137 --> 13:11.747
Yes. In China.

13:11.791 --> 13:13.749
With me as his cellmate.

13:13.793 --> 13:15.316
Social engineering.

13:15.359 --> 13:17.535
We gain his trust,
get him to talk a little bit.

13:17.579 --> 13:19.581
Perhaps he even gives up
the, uh,

13:19.624 --> 13:21.104
location of Codex without him

13:21.148 --> 13:22.845
even realizing it.

13:22.889 --> 13:27.719
I'll be the Phoenix agent
who pursues him, and once

13:27.763 --> 13:30.418
we are trapped together,
I'll become his confidant.

13:30.461 --> 13:32.463
It should be me.

13:35.249 --> 13:37.569
The Merchant needs to believe
that his cellmate is an ally.

13:37.599 --> 13:40.297
And Codex's master planwas designed by...

13:40.341 --> 13:42.517
my mother.

13:42.560 --> 13:44.867
And... my aunt
runs the place, so,

13:44.911 --> 13:46.869
Codex is practically
the family business.

13:46.913 --> 13:48.479
No, Mac.

13:48.523 --> 13:51.918
You've been through
a lot lately, and, um...

13:51.961 --> 13:55.008
this hits a bit close to home.Exactly.

13:55.051 --> 13:56.792
It'll make it more convincing.

13:56.836 --> 13:59.490
Look, I've run this con before
with MI6.

14:00.535 --> 14:02.102
I have experience.

14:02.145 --> 14:03.364
Ican handle this.

14:03.407 --> 14:04.756
You're not strong enough.

14:04.800 --> 14:06.889
Look, forgive me, but

14:06.933 --> 14:08.345
after everything you've
been through recently,

14:08.369 --> 14:10.371
I just don't think
that you have the...

14:10.414 --> 14:11.763
Don't have the what?

14:11.807 --> 14:15.202
The mental stability
that this requires.

14:20.294 --> 14:21.773
You're right.

14:23.471 --> 14:25.536
I'm not sleeping, and I can't
stop thinking about Codex,

14:25.560 --> 14:27.200
or the people
that they want to sacrifice.

14:28.955 --> 14:30.870
Or the people that
I've lost, so...

14:30.913 --> 14:33.829
Let me use it, please.

14:35.483 --> 14:36.939
If The Merchant's emotional
intelligence is as high

14:36.963 --> 14:38.375
as you say,
then he's gonna look at me,

14:38.399 --> 14:39.966
and he's gonna see
a kindred spirit.

14:40.009 --> 14:42.969
Someone who's pushed to the
edge, just trying to survive.

14:54.458 --> 14:56.460
You'll need to look the part.

14:58.201 --> 15:00.595
We'll suggest
you two were drugged,

15:00.638 --> 15:02.249
which will account
for the lost time,

15:02.292 --> 15:03.598
and provide physical evidence

15:03.641 --> 15:05.382
that'll seem too insane to fake.

15:05.426 --> 15:08.995
When we abducted him, we found
anti-anxiety medication.

15:09.038 --> 15:11.780
Withholding that will
throw him off his game.

15:11.823 --> 15:13.434
Bozer will head up
production design.

15:13.477 --> 15:15.958
Layer the dirt on those walls.
This is all about the details.

15:16.002 --> 15:17.786
Where's my rodent guy?

15:17.829 --> 15:19.875
We'll need the proper lighting
and atmosphere.

15:19.919 --> 15:21.877
This rig will use nanoparticlesto compress

15:21.921 --> 15:23.899
what happens to sunlightas
it passes through the Earth's

15:23.923 --> 15:26.969
atmosphere over six miles
down into a few feet.

15:27.013 --> 15:29.078
We'll have surveillance,
but you'll be in close quarters

15:29.102 --> 15:32.192
with The Merchant, so
that means no comms. You need

15:32.235 --> 15:34.063
to establish a rapport.

15:34.107 --> 15:36.196
Normally, I'd say use

15:36.239 --> 15:38.328
emotive mirroring, active listening,

15:38.372 --> 15:40.156
but we're short on time, so,

15:40.200 --> 15:41.636
get him to tell you his name.

15:41.679 --> 15:43.116
All right.

16:02.918 --> 16:05.007
Hello, Clive.

16:05.051 --> 16:07.357
They messed you up
pretty good, huh?

16:07.401 --> 16:10.534
Did you find out where we are?

16:10.578 --> 16:11.927
Who they are?

16:11.971 --> 16:13.711
What-what they want from us?

16:15.757 --> 16:18.716
We're being heldby China's Ministry

16:18.760 --> 16:21.937
of State Security.

16:21.981 --> 16:23.983
The secret police.

16:24.026 --> 16:26.855
Yeah. They think
we're Western spies.

16:26.898 --> 16:29.031
Well, you area Western spy.

16:29.075 --> 16:31.077
Yeah.

16:31.120 --> 16:34.036
Well... I was.

16:34.080 --> 16:36.038
How so?

16:36.082 --> 16:39.085
I defected from the Phoenix.

16:39.128 --> 16:41.652
And I've been tracking you

16:41.696 --> 16:44.394
because I need your help...

16:44.438 --> 16:46.701
making contact with Titan.

16:52.098 --> 16:54.448
And why on earth would you wantto do that?

16:54.491 --> 16:57.799
So that I can join Codex.

16:57.842 --> 17:00.062
He pushed it.
That was too early.

17:00.106 --> 17:02.064
No, no, no, he's good.
He's gonna bite.

17:02.108 --> 17:04.762
Listen to me. Level with me.

17:04.806 --> 17:06.460
The Phoenix Foundation...

17:06.503 --> 17:08.244
They're really not coming
for you?

17:10.159 --> 17:12.031
Definitely not.

17:13.989 --> 17:16.600
Well, I can't tell you
how happy that makes me.

17:16.644 --> 17:18.994
But you know, there's
an easy-peasy solution

17:19.038 --> 17:20.952
to all of this, right?

