18:32.111 --> 18:33.895
One, two, three.

18:33.938 --> 18:35.026
Parrotbill.

18:37.072 --> 18:39.205
Four, five.

18:39.248 --> 18:40.728
Bunting.

18:42.338 --> 18:44.819
One, two, three. Parrotbill.

19:06.232 --> 19:07.842
What the devil
is Clive playing at?

19:07.885 --> 19:08.973
The kind of stuff

19:09.017 --> 19:11.411
you dowhen you're crazy banana pants?

19:11.454 --> 19:12.736
What are we gonna do
about the stun gun?

19:12.760 --> 19:14.283
The Merchant mentionedlifting it,

19:14.327 --> 19:16.167
but he's gonna know
pretty soonif it's a fake.

19:16.198 --> 19:17.610
Which is why it won't be.
DESI: We're gonna give

19:17.634 --> 19:19.419
a real weapon
to the Downton Abbeyreject

19:19.462 --> 19:20.744
in there? MATTY: No, we're not gonna

19:20.768 --> 19:22.857
do that,
because that's too dangerous.

19:22.900 --> 19:25.294
Look, The Merchant thinks that
Mac's gonna help him escape.

19:25.338 --> 19:26.774
He won't hurt him.

19:26.817 --> 19:29.211
It's a risk
we're gonna have to take.

19:29.255 --> 19:31.344
Right.

19:31.387 --> 19:34.129
Time for sunset.

19:34.173 --> 19:35.391
But it's only beena few hours

19:35.435 --> 19:36.827
in that cell since sunrise.

19:36.871 --> 19:39.526
Yes, well, I'm throwing
off his circadian rhythms,

19:39.569 --> 19:41.049
adding a lightning storm

19:41.092 --> 19:44.792
and dosing his dinner with his

19:44.835 --> 19:46.576
anti-anxiety medication.

19:46.620 --> 19:49.797
The benzo hit should
triggerfeelings of tranquility,

19:49.840 --> 19:51.755
and make him trust Maceven more.

19:51.799 --> 19:55.455
Something about youplaying God is...
terrifying.

19:55.498 --> 19:56.891
Well, it is a chess match.

19:56.934 --> 19:58.477
We have to do whatever
we can to make sure

19:58.501 --> 20:00.895
that Mac is not the pawn.

20:14.778 --> 20:16.345
I can't bear awkward silences.

20:18.173 --> 20:21.132
Listen, why don't you tell me
a little bit about yourself?

20:21.176 --> 20:24.832
I'm just interested to know... what
makes the Boy Wonder tick?

20:26.181 --> 20:27.922
Seriously, what...?

20:29.184 --> 20:30.968
What are your hopes?
What are your dreams?

20:31.012 --> 20:33.144
To get you to stop talking.

20:33.188 --> 20:35.886
Just tell me one thing.

20:35.930 --> 20:37.714
Why do you want to meet Titan?

20:38.802 --> 20:41.805
Why would you want to go
face-to-face

20:41.849 --> 20:45.113
with the architect
of Codex's doomsday plans?

20:45.156 --> 20:48.116
She's my aunt.

20:48.159 --> 20:50.161
Like hell she is.

20:57.038 --> 20:58.822
You're telling the truth?

20:58.866 --> 21:00.911
I really wish I wasn't.

21:00.955 --> 21:03.479
So it's a family matter.

21:06.177 --> 21:08.092
Well, what do

21:08.136 --> 21:09.659
your parents say? Do they know?

21:10.704 --> 21:12.706
Siblings?

21:15.752 --> 21:18.233
I see. None of those.

21:18.277 --> 21:21.018
So...

21:21.062 --> 21:23.456
you're all alone in the world.

21:25.806 --> 21:27.677
I wouldn't say that.

21:27.721 --> 21:29.853
Listen,
family's important, but...

21:29.897 --> 21:31.333
Even if you don't get along.

21:31.377 --> 21:33.030
But when they're gone,

21:33.074 --> 21:36.033
well, it's like you're-you're
the last of your kind.

21:36.077 --> 21:38.732
Literally. You're like
an endangered species.

21:39.994 --> 21:42.475
It's just you,

21:42.518 --> 21:45.304
left to wander the wilderness

21:45.347 --> 21:48.698
until you finally die
and become extinct.

21:49.743 --> 21:51.484
I want to pull Macout of there.

21:51.527 --> 21:53.268
It's too soon.
They're building trust.

21:53.312 --> 21:54.985
No, he's losing control
of the conversation.

21:55.009 --> 21:56.271
Give us the room.

22:01.581 --> 22:03.713
You said you did this op at MI6.

22:04.758 --> 22:06.020
I did.

22:06.063 --> 22:07.456
And?

22:07.500 --> 22:09.066
It was successful.

22:11.025 --> 22:12.896
Until it wasn't.

22:12.940 --> 22:14.613
I locked one of our best
operational officers in

22:14.637 --> 22:16.683
with a terrorist in the hope
of getting some intel

22:16.726 --> 22:19.033
on an upcoming attack.

22:19.076 --> 22:20.121
What happened?

22:20.164 --> 22:22.602
My officer's jugular
was sliced open

22:22.645 --> 22:24.168
with a shard of broken glass.

22:24.212 --> 22:26.388
We...

22:26.432 --> 22:28.042
we missed it.

22:28.085 --> 22:30.392
And now we're gonna put a
weaponin The Merchant's hands.

22:30.436 --> 22:32.829
But we managed to getenough
intel to stop the attack.

22:32.873 --> 22:35.354
Taylor, I know you well enough
now to know.

22:35.397 --> 22:37.094
You're worried.

22:37.138 --> 22:41.011
Which is why I want to
pull Macout of there.

22:41.055 --> 22:43.492
She told me about
you once, you know.

22:43.536 --> 22:45.146
'Course, I didn't
know at the time

22:45.189 --> 22:47.017
that youwere the famous nephew.

22:47.061 --> 22:48.323
What do you mean?

22:48.367 --> 22:49.933
Auntie Gwen.

22:49.977 --> 22:51.674
Oh, uh, um, we're not close

22:51.718 --> 22:52.999
or any...
Actually, she doesn't like...

22:53.023 --> 22:54.460
Actually, she wants to kill me.

22:54.503 --> 22:55.896
What did she say?

22:55.939 --> 22:57.352
Well, as you know,
she's so dedicated

22:57.376 --> 22:59.334
to saving the world from itself.

22:59.378 --> 23:02.990
I was curious to find out why.

23:03.033 --> 23:04.948
So I asked her.

23:04.992 --> 23:07.429
And she told me.

23:07.473 --> 23:10.693
She said... and I quote...

23:10.737 --> 23:13.783
"I want my nephew to have
a long and beautiful life.

23:13.827 --> 23:16.482
"And I want that
for his children

23:16.525 --> 23:19.006
and for his
children's children."

23:19.049 --> 23:19.920
Me?

23:19.963 --> 23:22.226
Me? I'm all about survival.

23:22.270 --> 23:24.751
Is that how you got back
with Codex,

23:24.794 --> 23:25.926
back in their...

23:25.969 --> 23:27.971
good graces?

23:30.757 --> 23:31.975
Well, I mustn't lie.

23:32.019 --> 23:34.456
I've got a certain skill set
that they need,

23:34.500 --> 23:38.155
and that's reserved me a seatin
the doomsday bunker, luckily.

23:40.070 --> 23:43.030
Did you hear that?

23:43.073 --> 23:44.466
They have a doomsday bunker.

23:44.510 --> 23:45.685
Already on it.

23:45.728 --> 23:47.271
Tracking all shipments
from the past year

23:47.295 --> 23:50.994
of materials needed to build
afortified underground structure.

23:51.038 --> 23:52.648
Good job, Mac.

23:52.692 --> 23:54.824
Old Clive is giving up
valuable intel,

23:54.868 --> 23:56.565
and he doesn't even realize it.

23:56.609 --> 23:58.001
A doomsday bunker?

23:58.045 --> 24:00.134
How long do we have
to get into that thing?

24:02.963 --> 24:04.573
Time-out.

24:05.618 --> 24:07.837
Why?

24:07.881 --> 24:11.101
Why now? Why-why do you...

24:11.145 --> 24:13.930
want to join Codex now?

24:28.815 --> 24:32.166
My whole life,
I've been a Boy Scout.

24:34.560 --> 24:37.911
Trying to make my... saintly

24:37.954 --> 24:39.913
dead mom proud.

24:39.956 --> 24:42.263
But now that I know
the truth about her

24:42.306 --> 24:46.049
and both of my parents
are dead...

24:48.138 --> 24:49.923
I feel...

24:49.966 --> 24:51.968
free.

24:54.188 --> 24:57.713
Free to choosethe path
of science and reason.

24:57.757 --> 25:00.716
And the whole...

25:00.760 --> 25:04.328
"Codex planningon killing
billions of people"?

25:05.373 --> 25:07.549
Your friends.

25:07.593 --> 25:09.986
Phoenix.

25:10.030 --> 25:12.859
Your girlfriend.

25:14.861 --> 25:16.993
What, that doesn't bother you?

25:17.037 --> 25:19.169
Sometimes, to do what's right,

25:19.213 --> 25:22.129
you have to sacrifice
the things you love.

25:23.173 --> 25:25.219
Is that part of the act?

25:25.262 --> 25:27.221
Well, let's hope so.

25:27.264 --> 25:28.788
Enough with the sharing.

25:29.876 --> 25:32.269
Let's set this breakout
in motion, hmm?

25:37.579 --> 25:39.015
Uh, just...

25:46.545 --> 25:48.024
Thing is,
I haven't learned Mandarin

25:48.068 --> 25:49.915
since the last time you were
in here, so I've got no idea

25:49.939 --> 25:51.854
what you're talking about.

25:52.855 --> 25:54.814
Thanks.

25:54.857 --> 25:56.835
I take it you guys ran withthe
whole prison breakout thing,

25:56.859 --> 25:58.078
came up with a plan? Yeah.

25:58.121 --> 25:59.272
Bozer's waiting in the lab
to brief you.

25:59.296 --> 26:01.255
Mac, mate, are you okay?

26:01.298 --> 26:02.343
Yeah, I'm fine.

26:02.386 --> 26:04.693
Ready for a few more cutsand bruises.

26:17.140 --> 26:18.533
Well, well, well.

26:18.577 --> 26:22.189
You seem to be rather
goodat withstanding torture.

26:24.583 --> 26:26.062
So do you.

26:26.106 --> 26:28.587
Mm. Mm-hmm.

26:28.630 --> 26:30.589
Anyhoo,

26:30.632 --> 26:31.938
got you a little gift, didn't I?

26:31.981 --> 26:34.505
Yeah.

26:34.549 --> 26:37.726
Saw it in the windowand I thought of you.

26:37.770 --> 26:38.727
Oh, bloody hell.

26:38.771 --> 26:40.511
It works.Shocking.

26:41.556 --> 26:43.297
All right. This time.

26:43.340 --> 26:45.821
Oh! Watch out, watch out.

26:45.865 --> 26:47.040
It is sensitive.

26:49.042 --> 26:51.566
Well, this is
a charged moment, isn't it?

26:55.048 --> 26:56.658
Sorry, I couldn't resist.

26:56.702 --> 26:58.355
You're no fun at all.

27:12.326 --> 27:15.198
Maybe you could explain to
mehow destroying our only weapon

27:15.242 --> 27:16.722
is gonna get us out of here.

27:16.765 --> 27:19.463
Gas cartridge plus needle...

27:19.507 --> 27:22.771
equals lock pick gun.

27:22.815 --> 27:24.860
A weapon is no use to us

27:24.904 --> 27:26.949
if we can't get out of here.

27:26.993 --> 27:28.734
Yeah, but a lock pickisn't gonna help us

27:28.777 --> 27:30.431
take out the guards, is it?

27:30.474 --> 27:32.999
No reason we can't have both.

27:34.304 --> 27:36.698
Now, most projectile stun guns,

27:36.742 --> 27:40.267
they have a direct
contact backup feature

27:40.310 --> 27:43.226
in case the cartridges
have been deployed.

27:44.184 --> 27:46.752
And you're arming me.

27:46.795 --> 27:49.145
Is that wise?

27:49.189 --> 27:50.862
You're an opportunist
who wants to capitalize

27:50.886 --> 27:53.193
on bringing me to Titan.

27:53.236 --> 27:55.674
I think it makes sense.

27:55.717 --> 27:58.024
Let's just call it trust, shall we?

27:59.678 --> 28:02.463
Pretty impressive skills, by the way.

28:03.638 --> 28:06.946
Gonna need those
as we cross into Zavkhan.

28:06.989 --> 28:09.949
He just dropped the name of
a remote province in Mongolia.

28:09.992 --> 28:11.124
I can cross-reference that

28:11.167 --> 28:13.082
with fallout shelter
material shipments

28:13.126 --> 28:14.736
and construction activity.

28:14.780 --> 28:16.477
Could give us a solid
location on Codex.

28:16.520 --> 28:19.262
Sir, there's a linein the
transcript from earlier

28:19.306 --> 28:21.284
that voice recognitionlogged as
inaudible... I'm busy right now.

28:21.308 --> 28:22.938
I checked the video,
just to cover our bases,

28:22.962 --> 28:25.747
and I found this.

28:25.791 --> 28:28.141
One, two, three, parrotbill...

28:28.184 --> 28:30.796
four, five...

28:30.839 --> 28:31.797
bunting.

28:31.840 --> 28:33.494
Cut the lines!

28:33.537 --> 28:35.235
The Internet!
The satellite!

28:35.278 --> 28:36.976
Cut the connection!
Seal us off now!

28:37.019 --> 28:39.108
What is it? What? What?
The Merchant is onto us.

28:39.152 --> 28:40.588
I don't know by how much,

28:40.631 --> 28:41.870
but he at least suspectsthat
he's been in a simulation.

28:41.894 --> 28:43.504
The intel he sent us is a trap.

28:43.547 --> 28:44.897
Okay, okay.
Just take a breath.

28:44.940 --> 28:45.898
Phoenix's network is protected

28:45.941 --> 28:48.422
by a sandboxed API, VPN, IDS.

28:48.465 --> 28:50.380
We should be o... What?

28:50.424 --> 28:51.860
Oh, this is never good. What is it?

28:51.904 --> 28:53.098
Someone got through
and pinged us.

28:53.122 --> 28:54.733
The Merchant sucked us
into this whole

28:54.776 --> 28:56.169
stun gun thing to get

28:56.212 --> 28:58.780
our focus away from
the real risk, the fake intel.

28:58.824 --> 28:59.888
Looks like someone beat
our network.

28:59.912 --> 29:01.217
My money's on Codex.

29:01.261 --> 29:02.610
He used us

29:02.653 --> 29:03.654
to send them an SOS.

29:03.698 --> 29:05.178
"Zavkhan" and "bunker"

29:05.221 --> 29:06.483
are trigger words.

29:06.527 --> 29:07.852
Anyone searchingfor those
words on the Internet

29:07.876 --> 29:09.269
will send an alarmto Codex.

29:09.312 --> 29:10.725
Anyone who sees the
networkwill know it's us.

29:10.749 --> 29:12.074
He's too valuable
of an asset to them.

29:12.098 --> 29:13.490
They're not gonna give him up.

29:13.534 --> 29:15.454
But if they have our location...
Codex is coming.

29:21.847 --> 29:24.545
♪

29:24.588 --> 29:27.591
Ten minutes ago,
someone searched keywords,

29:27.635 --> 29:30.072
triggering a distress beacon
in Los Angeles.

29:30.116 --> 29:32.074
We believe it to be
an asset of ours

29:32.118 --> 29:34.120
known simply as "The Merchant."

29:34.163 --> 29:39.081
We believe that he's being
heldby the Phoenix Foundation.

29:39.125 --> 29:41.997
Now, Titan wants him alive,

29:42.041 --> 29:45.131
by any means necessary.

29:45.174 --> 29:46.741
Are we clear?

29:46.785 --> 29:48.177
Yes, ma'am.

29:48.221 --> 29:49.526
Load up.

29:51.050 --> 29:54.836
I want to tell you something
in all honesty, which is

29:54.880 --> 29:56.727
a rare commodity; I mean,
it's an undervalued trait

29:56.751 --> 29:58.013
in today's society.

29:58.057 --> 29:59.425
Can't you just say
somethingwithout a preamble?

29:59.449 --> 30:01.843
Well, I can, but
I discovered years ago

30:01.887 --> 30:05.673
the pretty words make my
personality more palatable.

30:05.716 --> 30:07.762
Strange as it may sound,

30:07.806 --> 30:09.851
I actually have
high hopes for you.

30:09.895 --> 30:12.027
More than that,
I have faith in you.

30:12.071 --> 30:14.377
You will be free.

30:14.421 --> 30:17.772
I think you're gonna
make a great leader.

30:17.816 --> 30:20.122
And I think you're gonna
save an awful lot of people.

30:20.166 --> 30:22.777
At least I hope so.

30:22.821 --> 30:24.039
For both our sakes.

30:26.085 --> 30:27.869
All right, so... chance.

30:27.913 --> 30:28.977
Wait for 'em to go by again,

30:29.001 --> 30:30.959
then we take 'em by surprise.Okay.

30:32.178 --> 30:34.876
